<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Currently the XML generated by Zend_Rest_Server includes the class and method names called by the Zend_Rest_Server instance. This causes potential security concerns as it exposes the private details of the implementation.</p>

<p>For example, from the output:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
1Car2Trucksuccess</code></pre>

<p>One can gather that it was generated with Zend Framework using the call Test_Service_Product::getRecent.</p>

<p>Zend_Rest_Server should provide the option to only output the data as XML:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
1Car2Truck</code></pre>

